    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>per Steamer via <placeName>Halifax</placeName></p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                <date>18th Jany 1864</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Revd. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I take leave to address you the<lb/> present to request if you will
                kindly oblige me to<lb/> have printed for me, in Hebrew, twenty five copies<lb/> of
                the seven verses of the Akafot read at burials;<lb/> affixed, should it not cost
                more than 25 cents each<lb/> or $6.25/00 for the 25 copies. The size of each
                copy<lb/> must be exactly that of the <sic>inclosed</sic> slip of paper<lb/>
                consequently it will admit a good size type as I would<lb/> desire the entire size
                of the paper to be made use of<lb/> leaving no blank space below, except the margin
                &amp; the<lb/> space required between each verse. Please let the<lb/> quality of the
                paper be as good &amp; stout as the enclosed<lb/> piece, or better if possible.
                Please when sending the<lb/> same not to fold the paper as they are intended<lb/> to
                be pasted on boards to read by at the Bet Haim,<lb/> but put them up in a roll
                securely tied &amp; sealed &amp;<lb/> put the parcel in the ship's letter bag should
                there<lb/> be one direct or via <placeName>New York</placeName>, addressing the<lb/>
                said parcel to me &amp; writing on it “papers”.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The amount of this small commission I<lb/> will immediately on
                receipt of your advice pay over<lb/> to any party here you may desire. I trust
                you</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>will excuse the trouble this small commission will<lb/> occasion you, it being for a
                religious purpose &amp;<lb/> required for the congregation, of which I am at present
                the<lb/> vice president whose <del>duty</del> office is to look after these<lb/>
                matters connected with funerals. Relying that<lb/> you will forward this small
                commission as early<lb/> as possible &amp; awaiting your reply.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With sentiments of the highest respect</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your Most obdt Servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">B Delvalle</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. Should you have any parcel sending to any party here<lb/> you may if you
                please, include the above.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>per Steamer via <placeName>Halifax</placeName></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
